<h1 style="width: 370px">Binding to Data with AdapterView——使用AdapterView绑定到数据</h1>
</div>

  <div id="jd-content">


    <div class="jd-descr">
    <div id="qv-wrapper">
<div id="qv">
  <h2>In this document——这篇文档中</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><a href="#FillingTheLayout">Filling the Layout with Data</a>——向布局中填充数据</li>
    <li><a href="#HandlingUserSelections">Handling User Selections</a>——响应用户选择</li>
  </ol>
  
  <h2>See also——您还可以参考</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><a href="../../../guide/tutorials/views/hello-spinner.html">Hello Spinner tutorial</a></li>
    <li><a href="../../../guide/tutorials/views/hello-listview.html">Hello ListView tutorial</a></li>
    <li><a href="../../../guide/tutorials/views/hello-gridview.html">Hello GridView tutorial</a></li>
  </ol>
</div>
</div>

<p>The <code><a href="../../../reference/android/widget/AdapterView.html">AdapterView</a></code> is a ViewGroup subclass whose child Views are determined by an <code><a href="../../../reference/android/widget/Adapter.html">Adapter</a></code> that 
binds to data of some type. AdapterView is useful whenever you need to display stored data (as opposed to resource strings or drawables) in your layout.<br>
<code><a href="../../../reference/android/widget/AdapterView.html">AdapterView</a></code>是一个可视框组的子类，这个子类的子可视框由一个绑定到某种类型的数据的<code><a href="../../../reference/android/widget/Adapter.html">Adapter</a></code>决定。AdapterView用于在布局中您显示存储的数据（而不是资源或可绘制的）。</p>

<p><code><a href="../../../reference/android/widget/Gallery.html">Gallery</a></code>, <code><a href="../../../reference/android/widget/ListView.html">ListView</a></code>, and  <code><a href="../../../reference/android/widget/Spinner.html">Spinner</a></code> are examples of AdapterView subclasses that you can use to bind to a specific type of data and display it in a certain way. 
<br>
<code><a href="../../../reference/android/widget/Gallery.html">Gallery</a></code>, <code><a href="../../../reference/android/widget/ListView.html">ListView</a></code>和<code><a href="../../../reference/android/widget/Spinner.html">Spinner</a></code>是AdapterView子类的例子，您可以使用它们绑定到特殊类型的数据，并以特定方式显示。</p>


<p>AdapterView objects have two main responsibilities: <br>
AdapterView对象有两种主要用途：</p>
<ul>
    <li>Filling the layout with data
    ——向布局中填充数据</li>
    <li>Handling user selections
    ——响应用户选择</li>
</ul>


<h2 id="FillingTheLayout">Filling the Layout with Data——向布局中填充数据</h2>
<p>Inserting data into the layout is typically done by binding the AdapterView class to an <code><a href="../../../reference/android/widget/Adapter.html">Adapter</a></code>, which retireves data from an external source (perhaps a list that
the code supplies or query results from the device's database). <br>
向布局中插入数据典型的做法是将AdapterView绑定到一个<code><a href="../../../reference/android/widget/Adapter.html">Adapter</a></code>，<code><a href="../../../reference/android/widget/Adapter.html">Adapter</a></code>从外部资源（可能是代码支持的一个列表或者是设备数据库的请求回应）进行数据的获取。</p>
<p>The following code sample does the following:<br>
下面的代码做下面两件事：</p>
<ol>
  <li>Creates a <code><a href="../../../reference/android/widget/Spinner.html">Spinner</a></code> with an existing View and binds it to a new ArrayAdapter
that reads an array of colors from the local resources.<br>
	使用一个已有的View创建一个<code><a href="../../../reference/android/widget/Spinner.html">Spinner</a></code>然后将其绑定到一个新的从本地资源读取颜色列表的ArrayAdapter。</li>
  <li>Creates another Spinner object from a View and binds it to a new SimpleCursorAdapter that will read 
people's names from the device contacts (see <code><a href="../../../reference/android/provider/Contacts.People.html">Contacts.People</a></code>).<br>
	从一个View创建另一个Spinner 对象，然后将其绑定到一个新的从设备通讯录读取联系人名字（参见<code><a href="../../../reference/android/provider/Contacts.People.html">Contacts.People</a></code>）的SimpleCursorAdapter。</li>
</ol>

<pre>
// Get a Spinner and bind it to an ArrayAdapter that 
// references a String array.
Spinner s1 = (Spinner) findViewById(R.id.spinner1);
ArrayAdapter<CharSequence> adapter = ArrayAdapter.createFromResource(
    this, R.array.colors, android.R.layout.simple_spinner_item);
adapter.setDropDownViewResource(android.R.layout.simple_spinner_dropdown_item);
s1.setAdapter(adapter);

// Load a Spinner and bind it to a data query.
private static String[] PROJECTION = new String[] {
        People._ID, People.NAME
    };

Spinner s2 = (Spinner) findViewById(R.id.spinner2);
Cursor cur = managedQuery(People.CONTENT_URI, PROJECTION, null, null);
     
SimpleCursorAdapter adapter2 = new SimpleCursorAdapter(this,
    android.R.layout.simple_spinner_item, // Use a template
                                          // that displays a
                                          // text view
    cur, // Give the cursor to the list adatper
    new String[] {People.NAME}, // Map the NAME column in the
                                         // people database to...
    new int[] {android.R.id.text1}); // The "text1" view defined in
                                     // the XML template
					 
adapter2.setDropDownViewResource(android.R.layout.simple_spinner_dropdown_item);
s2.setAdapter(adapter2);
</pre>

<p>Note that it is necessary to have the People._ID column in projection used with CursorAdapter
or else you will get an exception.</p>
	<p>注意： CursorAdapter 使用得项目中必须有People._ID一栏，否则会得到一个异常。</p>

<p>If, during the course of your application's life, you change the underlying data that is read by your Adapter,
you should call <code><a href="../../../reference/android/widget/ArrayAdapter.html#notifyDataSetChanged()">notifyDataSetChanged()</a></code>. This will notify the attached View
that the data has been changed and it should refresh itself.<br>
如果，在您的应用程序生存时间内，改变了Adapter使用的底层的数据，您应该调用<code><a href="../../../reference/android/widget/ArrayAdapter.html#notifyDataSetChanged()">notifyDataSetChanged()</a></code>。这个方法通知数据绑定到的View，数据已经改变，应该刷新。</p>

<h2 id="HandlingUserSelections">Handling User Selections——响应用户的选择</h2>
<p>You handle the user's selecction by setting the class's <code><a href="../../../reference/android/widget/AdapterView.OnItemClickListener.html">AdapterView.OnItemClickListener</a></code> member to a listener and
catching the selection changes. <br>
您可以通过设定类的<code><a href="../../../reference/android/widget/AdapterView.OnItemClickListener.html">AdapterView.OnItemClickListener</a></code>成员来监听和捕获选择的变化。</p>
<pre>
// Create a message handling object as an anonymous class.
private OnItemClickListener mMessageClickedHandler = new OnItemClickListener() {
    public void onItemClick(AdapterView parent, View v, int position, long id)
    {
        // Display a messagebox.
        Toast.makeText(mContext,"You've got an event",Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
    }
};

// Now hook into our object and set its onItemClickListener member
// to our class handler object.
mHistoryView = (ListView)findViewById(R.id.history);
mHistoryView.setOnItemClickListener(mMessageClickedHandler); 
</pre>

<div class="special">
<p>For more discussion on how to create different AdapterViews, read the following tutorials:
<a href="../../../guide/tutorials/views/hello-spinner.html">Hello Spinner</a>,
<a href="../../../guide/tutorials/views/hello-listview.html">Hello ListView</a>, and
<a href="../../../guide/tutorials/views/hello-gridview.html">Hello GridView</a>.
<br>
更多关于如何创建不同类型的AdapterViews的讨论，请阅读下列指南：<a href="../../../guide/tutorials/views/hello-spinner.html">Hello Spinner</a>,
<a href="../../../guide/tutorials/views/hello-listview.html">Hello ListView</a>,和<a href="../../../guide/tutorials/views/hello-gridview.html">Hello GridView</a>。</div>

